DUMP / SDUMP / LDUMP / PDUMP
  Machine-readable data dumps for external tools and scripts.

SYNTAX
  dump              sector dump (all your sectors)
  sdump             ship dump (all your ships)
  ldump             land unit dump
  pdump             plane dump

DESCRIPTION
  Outputs game data in a fixed-column machine-readable format
  intended for client-side tools (parsers, bots, map display).

  dump  — all sector fields for owned sectors, one row per sector.
          Includes coordinates, designations, efficiency, all item
          counts, delivery/threshold settings, and terrain data.

  sdump — all ship fields: uid, owner, x, y, type, efficiency,
          mobility, tech, fleet letter.

  ldump/pdump — same concept for land units and planes (stub output
          if no units exist).

  The first line after the header is a column-name row.
  Subsequent rows are data.  The final line gives the record count.

  Use 'census', 'ship', 'commodity' for human-readable output.

EXAMPLE
  dump                      full sector dump
  sdump                     ship dump
  pdump                     plane dump

